{
  "texts": [
    "These equalities imply the following duality: SO(2N)|USp(2M) NS5-type interface ⇔ SO(2N)|SO(2M + 1) D5 ′ -type interface, (3.62) which generalizes (3.51) with gauge groups of equal rank.",
    "Moreover, the half-index (3.55) for the NS5 ′ -type SO(2N) -|USp(2M) coincides with the half-index (3.59) for N > M and the half-index (3.61) for N < M!",
    "This supports the duality of interfaces involving the disconnected O(2N) gauge group O(2N)|USp(2M) NS5-type interface ⇔ O(2N)|SO(2M + 1) D5 ′ -type interface.",
    "(3.63) In the Coulomb limit and Higgs limit the half-indices (3.58) and (3.59) become Figure 8.8Figure 8.",
    "(a) The maximal giant gravitons in AdS 5 × S 5."
